    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/24982 caused a regression, where some characters and highlights are missing. \r\n\r\nThe most obvious case is when using the `indent-blankline.nvim` plugin, but I have seen broken up highlights using telescope, and missing characters in the built in terminal for example.\r\n\r\nFor example several characters at the start of the indentation are missing here\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/9946255/a686450e-e680-4548-9b9d-6886159fc5ec)\r\n And here's a broken telescope highlight\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/9946255/1b078f58-1925-41d0-bbe6-0e746ddc1aa5)\r\n\r\nThis happens both with `--multigrid` and without.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a file called `missing_chars.lua` with the following contents\r\n```lua\r\nfor name, url in pairs{\r\n   blankline = 'https://github.com/lukas-reineke/indent-blankline.nvim'\r\n} do\r\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/'..name, ':p')\r\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\r\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\r\n  end\r\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\r\nend\r\n\r\nrequire 'indent_blankline'.setup({})\r\n\r\nvim.opt.tabstop = 2\r\nvim.opt.shiftwidth = 2\r\nvim.opt.expandtab = true\r\n```\r\n2. run `neovide --neovim-bin path/to/nvim -- --clean -u missing_chars.lua missing_chars.lua`\r\n3. Observe that it looks like the screenshot above\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAll characters and highlights should be rendered correctly\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1029+gaf899971b\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nNeovide 0.11.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
